title: docs(ngSwitch): rectify the description
body: The previous one was incorrectly stating that “ngSwitch simply choses one of the nested elements and makes it visible”, which is not accurate: it actually removes or inserts the elements.

Add some nice module pages into the docs areas.

https://s3.amazonaws.com/angularjs-dev/docs-module-pages/docs/index.html

title: fix(ngShowHide): stop ngShow and ngHide applying animations incorrectly
body:
Fix ngShow and ngHide so they don't animate in/out their classes every time the watch expression is evaluated.  These directives now only change when the watch expression's boolean value actually changes.

Closes #4401

title: wrong link for services
body: i thought there might be api/ng/services so in lieu of that, the proposed link seems to have the intended information.

title: docs(guide/expression): fixing ng-repeater duplicate key error
body:
Issue occurs when the same expression is added twice or more. After that no new expressions can be added.

This can be resolved by adding: "track by $index" to ng-repeater. This way items are keyed by their position. For reference see:
http://docs.angularjs.org/error/ngRepeat:dupes

title: docs(ngClass): fix typo
body: demostrates -> demonstrates

title: docs(guide): rewrite guide landing page
body:
Change landing page to include a set of curated links with subject
headings as a guide through Angular's docs and other resources.

title: fix($injector): allow a constructor function to return a function
body:
This change makes `$injector.instantiate` (and thus `$provide.service`) to behave the same as native
`new` operator.

title: Fix(ng:repeat,ng:controller): Change priority order of ng:repeat and add priority to ng:controller
body:
Ensure priority is given to ng:controller when using ng:include/ng:repeat in conjuction with ng:controller.

Closes #4431
Closes #4521

milestone.description:
Issues and PRs for the release of AngularJS v1.2.2.

This milestone should only contain bug fixes and documentation updates.

title: Update step_02.ngdoc

fix(test): add beforeEach to load module

The non-global controller test throws an error because the test does not know about the module and so can not find the controller.  This change tells the test about the module so the test can find the controller.

title: docs($location): add documentation of $location's events
body:
Added documentation for $locationChangeStart and $locationChangeSuccess

Closes #1569

title: fix(csp): fix csp auto-detection and stylesheet injection
body:
When we refactored , we broke the csp mode because the previous implementation
relied on the fact that it was ok to lazy initialize the .csp property, this
is not the case any more.

Besides, we need to know about csp mode during bootstrap and avoid injecting the
stylesheet when csp is active, so I refactored the code to fix both issues.

PR #4411 will follow up on this commit and add more improvements.

Closes #917
Closes #2963
Closes #4394

title: fix(location): check for existence before using
body:

Partially fixes #4442

milestone.title: Docs Only
milestone.description:
Documentation only pull requests and issues can go in here.

This is a place to put PRs that are purely updating the documentation - i.e. no code changes.

When triaging I was putting such PRs into the next milestone, which at the moment would be 1.2.2 but I found that since these doc-fixes were not blocking releases, it was hiding how much real work was needed before the milestone was ready for the release.  

In effect, I created a parallel track for documentation updates.  Then when I had the time, I could sit down and knock off a dozen of these PRs at my leisure.
